\v 1 Blessed\f + \fr 1.1: \ft A nominal exclamation (IBHS 40.2.3.a).\f* is the man who
\q2 Does not walk\f + Qal, Per., 3, m, s; here Davidson sees perfect expressing an action that happened in the past but with continuing effects in the present (Davidson, Syntax §39.b).\f* in the counsel\f + \fr 1.1: \ft Syriac: inverse order (of clauses with second, that is, "way"?).\f* of the wicked,
\q2 And in the way of sin he does not stand,\f + Qal, Per., 3, m, s\f*
\q2 And in the seat of scoffers he does not sit.\f + Qal, Per, 3, m, s\f*
\q1
\v 2 But\f + \fr 1.2: \ft HALOT 471. See also Hebrew Bible Insert, par. 3.3.5g; GKC §163.b.\f* in the instruction of Yhwh is his delight
\q1 and on his instruction he meditates\f + Qal, Impf., 3, m, s\f* day and night.\f + \fr 1.2: \ft This is an example of an adverb and adverbial accusative together (IBHS 39.3.1.g).\f*
\q1
\v 3 \f + \fr 1.3: \ft Frequentive imperfect where English uses present (Davidson, Syntax §44.a).\f*He is\f + Qal, Per., 3, m, s\f* like a tree planted\f + \fr 1.3: \ft Qal Pass., Part., ms.\f* by streams of water,
\q1 which\f + \fr 1.3: \ft Missing in a fragment from Cairo Geniza.\f* gives\f + Qal, Impf., 3, m, s\f* it’s fruit in its season,
\q1 And its leaf does not wither,\f + Qal, Impf., 3, m, s, נבל\f*
\q1 And all he does\f + Qal, Impf., 3, m, s\f* he succeeds.\f + Hiph., Impf., 3, m, s\f*\f + \fr 1.3: \ft BHS suggests this is a gloss from Josh 1:8.\f*
\q1
\v 4 It is not so for the wicked,\f + \fr 1.4: \ft BHS suggests adding a second לא כן at the end of the line, following LXX. Also Arnold and Choi par. 2.6.5 note the generic use of the article for a class. See also IBHS 13.5.1.f.\f*
\q1 Rather\f + \fr 1.4: \ft HALOT 471.\f* he is like the chaff that\f + \fr 1.4: \ft Resumptive (IBHS 19.3.b).\f* the wind blows away.\f + Qal, Impf., 3, f, s, נדף.\f*
\q1
\v 5 Therefore the wicked\f + \fr 1.5: \ft Why no article? It is often not included in poetry, but it is plural (Davidson, Syntax §22.b).\f* shall not rise\f + Qal, Impf., 3, m, p\f* in the judgment,
\q1 Nor sinners in the assembly of the righteous.
\q1
